flowRoot.flowPara: In the public language use the term "Hacker" is often understood as a computer criminal. This is an invention by the media and is not true. The term "Hacker" has a long standing tradition from the 1960's on and the tradition of "Hacking" in the sense of playful experimenting is probably as old as mankind.

A "Hack" should be rather understood as an impromptu made in an unusual and sometimes unexpected and smart way. From trying improvised prototypes to building a production system with advanced features. The main aspect of a hack is playfulness, cleverness, and out-of-the-ordinory exploration and that you "Do It Youself" (DIY) instead of going the standard way or paying a professional.
You can find the place at the basement of Knossos University campus..
